data.description: A one-of-a-kind, late 1800s-era home with stunning mountain and valley views! This beautiful 3-bed, 2-bath Virginia City home is the perfect place to relax and enjoy the beauty of the Comstock. Upon arrival at the property, you’ll notice immediately the lovely covered front porch – the perfect spot to rest in the shade any time of year. Welcoming you inside the 2043 sq ft residence is an inviting family room with high ceilings and a fireplace with a pellet insert and stone surround. The well-appointed kitchen has all the modern conveniences, including a built-in dishwasher, built-in single oven, and breakfast nook. The master bedroom is on the main floor and has a walk-in closet and ensuite bathroom with jetted tub/shower combo. Upstairs, there is loft space that could be used as an office or hobby room. This home is situated on a gentle upslope, with partially landscaped front and back yards. The front yard has automatic sprinklers, and the back yard is fenced and has a storage shed – great for those who need extra storage space. This home is a rare find in Virginia City, and it's sure to turn heads. If you're looking for a unique and charming home with stunning mountain views, then this is the perfect place for you. Don’t miss an opportunity to see it for yourself while you still can – schedule your showing today!
